# Auto-commit after code changes

After making code changes in this project, create a git commit automatically when the work is complete.

- Do not wait for an explicit "commit" request unless the user says not to commit.
- Stage only files related to the task; exclude unrelated changes.
- Write a concise commit message focused on why the change was made.
- Do not push unless the user explicitly asks to push.
- Follow the git safety protocol: never amend pushed commits, never skip hooks, never commit secrets.

If there are no changes to commit, skip silently.
